    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect HARQ process number access in UL SCH CQI/RI handling\n\n### Summary\nThe functions `handle_ulsch_cqi_ri_pdu()` and `handle_ulsch_cqi_harq_ri_pdu()` were accessing the wrong struct member to retrieve the HARQ process number, causing incorrect behavior during UL transmission processing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SCHED/fapi_l1.c`: Fixed struct member access for HARQ process number in both functions\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions with ULSCH CQI/RI reporting, the eNB would incorrectly process HARQ information, leading to:\n- Segmentation faults when accessing invalid HARQ process IDs\n- Incorrect CQI/RI reporting handling\n- UL transmission failures for UEs using aperiodic CQI reporting\n\nThe issue manifests when processing UL_CONFIG.request messages containing ULSCH_CQI_RI_PDU or ULSCH_CQI_HARQ_RI_PDU types where the HARQ process number is accessed from the wrong PDU structure member.\n"
}